<section class="main-content main-margin">
    <h3 style="text-align: center"> We are a completely non-auditioning choir and orchestra welcoming members of all abilities, whether you're a serious musician or just looking for 
         a break from your studies, the more the merrier.
         The aim of our rehearsals is to have fun while making some pretty awesome music, so whatever your 
         degree, instrument or standard come and give us a go, we promise not to disappoint.</h3>
    <h2>Getting Started</h2>
    <h3>I'm new to Musical Medics</h3>
    <p>A very warm welcome to you. Go to <a href="~/AboutUs">About Us</a> to find out who we are, what we do and how you can get involved.</p>
    <h3>I'm Already a Member</h3>
    <p>Excellent! There's loads you can use our website for. If you haven't already, head over to our sister site the <a href="~/Library/">Music Library</a> to borrow music and suggest 
        and vote on your favourite pieces for our next concert. </br>
        Also check out our <a href="~/Events">Events</a> page to see what exciting events we have coming your way,
         and the <a href="~/Gallery">Gallery</a> where photos from our concerts and socials are regularly uploaded.</p>
    <h3>Contact Us</h3>
    <p style="padding-bottom: 35px">Join us on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/307200819293452/">Facebook</a> and follow us on <a href="https://twitter.com/EUMusicalMedics">Twitter</a>.
        </br>If you have any questions that aren't answered here we'd love to hear from you. Just drop us an e-mail at <b>edinburghmusicalmedics@gmail.com</b></br>
     </p>
    
</section>
         